%F A008284 T(n, k) = Sum_{i=1..k} T(n-k, i), for 1 <= k <= n-1; T(n, n) = 1 for n >= 1.
%F A008284 Or, T(n, 1) = T(n, n) = 1, T(n, k) = 0 (k > n), T(n, k) = T(n-1, k-1) + T(n-k, k).
%F A008284 G.f. for k-th column: x^k/(Product_{j=1..k} (1-x^j)). - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Nov 29 2000
%F A008284 G.f.: A(x, y) = Product_{n>=1} 1/(1-x^n)^(P_n(y)/n), where P_n(y) = Sum_{d|n} eulerphi(n/d)*y^d. - _Paul D. Hanna_, Jul 13 2004
%F A008284 If k >= n/2, T(n,k) = T(2(n-k),n-k) = A000041(n-k). - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Jan 12 2006  [Relation included by _Hans Loeblich_, Apr 16 2019, relation extended by _Evan Robinson_, Jun 30 2021]
%F A008284 G.f.: G(t,x) = -1 + 1/Product_{j>=1} (1-t*x^j). - _Emeric Deutsch_, Feb 12 2006
%F A008284 A002865(n) = Sum_{k=2..floor((n+2)/2)} T(n-k+1,k-1). - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Nov 04 2007
%F A008284 A000700(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} (-1)^(n-k) T(n,k). - _Jeremy L. Martin_, Jul 06 2013
%F A008284 G.f.: -1 + e^(F(x,z)), where F(x,z) = Sum_{n >= 1} (x*z)^n/(n*(1 - z^n)) is a g.f. for A126988. - _Peter Bala_, Jan 13 2015
%F A008284 Also, T(n, n-k) = k for k = 1, 2, 3; n >= 2k. T(n, 2) = floor(n/2). T(n, 3) = round(n^2/12). - _M. F. Hasler_, Sep 26 2017
%F A008284 T(n,k) = [n>0 & k>0] * (T(n-1,k-1) + T(n-k,k)) + [n==0 & k==0]. - _Robert A. Russell_, May 12 2018 from Knuth 7.2.1.4 (39)
%F A008284 T(n, k) = Sum_{i=0..n-1} T(n-ik-1, k-1) for k >= 1; T(-n, k) = 0 for n > 0; T(n, 0) = [n==0]. - _Joshua Swanson_ (writing for Juexian Li), May 24 2020
